Bauchi State Governor, Senator Bala Mohammed has flagged off the commencement of daily commercial flight by Max Air Transport Company from Bauchi to Abuja and vice versa. Speaking at the occasion held at Abubakar Tafawa Balewa International Airport, Bauchi, yesterday, Governor Mohammed expressed confidence that the development will bring to an end the aviation the transportation problem in the state. He said, “With this development, Bauchi state will witness an unprecedented boost in commerce and tourism sectors especially with the discovery of Oil in Alkaleri local government area of the state.” According to him, daily flights will also contribute immensely to the economic development of the state as Yankari Game Reserve will accordingly, play host to many national and international visitors. The Governor who said his administration has come up with the arrangement to assist people of the state who will now have their daily flights to improve their commercial activities.